{"type":"message","id":"5a0e2287","parentId":"76592a97","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:04:30.326Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_avf5aas0cdqx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 080317\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending TIC Experiment: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe current pulse is about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - the insight that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on last 20 pulse logs.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. First look at what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Then implement a simple TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me check the current directory structure and what's available.\r\n\r\nActually, as a stateless discontinuous agent, I should focus on ONE concrete action. The most impactful next step is to implement the TIC classifier experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me write a simple Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Classifies them\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create this in a new file `research/tic_experiment.py`.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script implementing the TIC classifier that will:\r\n1. Load last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extract n-gram features from each pulse\r\n3. Classify content as invariant (recurring) vs variant (unique)\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy\r\n5. Attempt next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nSANDBOX_ROOT = Path(__file__).parent.parent\r\nLOGS_DIR = SANDBOX_ROOT / \"logs\"\r\n\r\ndef extract_text_features(content: str) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-gram features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    # Normalize and tokenize\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_]{3,}\\b', content.lower())\r\n    bigrams = [f\"{words[i]}_{words[i+1]}\" for i in range(len(words)-1)]\r\n    trigrams = [f\"{words[i]}_{words[i+1]}_{words[i+2]}\" for i in range(len(words)-2)]\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'unigrams': Counter(words),\r\n        'bigrams': Counter(bigrams),\r\n        'trigrams': Counter(trigrams),\r\n        'word_count': len(words)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef identify_invariants(pulse_features: list, threshold: int = 2) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Find n-grams that appear across multiple pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n    # Aggregate n-gram counts across all pulses\r\n    unigram_counts = Counter()\r\n    bigram_counts = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for pf in pulse_features:\r\n        unigram_counts.update(pf['unigrams'])\r\n        bigram_counts.update(pf['bigrams'])\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants = n-grams appearing in threshold+ pulses\r\n    invariants = set()\r\n    for gram, count in unigram_counts.items():\r\n        if count >= threshold:\r\n            invariants.add(('u', gram))\r\n    for gram, count in bigram_counts.items():\r\n        if count >= threshold:\r\n            invariants.add(('b', gram))\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(features: dict, invariants: set) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    invariant_count = 0\r\n    variant_count = 0\r\n    \r\n    for unigram, count in features['unigrams'].items():\r\n        if ('u', unigram) in invariants:\r\n            invariant_count += count\r\n        else:\r\n            variant_count += count\r\n    \r\n    total = invariant_count + variant_count\r\n    if total == 0:\r\n        return {'invariant_ratio': 0.5, 'classification': 'unknown'}\r\n    \r\n    ratio = invariant_count / total\r\n    classification = 'invariant' if ratio > 0.5 else 'variant'\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant_ratio': ratio,\r\n        'classification': classification,\r\n        'invariant_count': invariant_count,\r\n        'variant_count': variant_count\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_features: dict, invariants: set) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict: given current pulse, what's likely in next pulse?\r\n    Key insight: invariants should persist; variants may shift\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    current_invariants = set()\r\n    for unigram in current_features['unigrams']:\r\n        if ('u', unigram) in invariants:\r\n            current_invariants.add(unigram)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'expected_invariants': list(current_invariants)[:10],\r\n        'persistence_score': len(current_invariants) / max(len(invariants), 1)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Main TIC experiment runner.\"\"\"\r\n    # Load last 20 pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[-20:]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        return {\"error\": f\"Need at least 5 pulses, found {len(pulse_files)}\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract features from each pulse\r\n    pulse_features = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        content = pf.read_text()\r\n        features =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Propos